# Muscle Building Program

**Start Date:** January 6, 2025
**Goal:** Lean bulk (70kg → 76-78kg by May 2025)
**Strategy:** +0.25kg/week, minimize fat gain

---

## Quick Reference

| Target | Value |
|--------|-------|
| **Calories** | 2,850 kcal/day |
| **Protein** | 154g (2.2g/kg) |
| **Carbs** | 180-210g (low-GI preferred) |
| **Fats** | 75-90g |
| **Creatine** | 5g/day |
| **Training** | 4 days/week |

---

## Daily Meal Structure

### Breakfast (before 10 AM) — 30-35g protein

> Protein before 10 AM enhances muscle protein synthesis (BMAL clock gene)

**Option A — Quick (5 min):**
- 3 eggs scrambled (18g protein)
- 1 Greek yogurt 170g (15-17g protein)
- 1 banana or berries
- *Total: ~35g protein, ~500 kcal*

**Option B — Ultra-Quick (2 min):**
- 2 Greek yogurts (30-34g protein)
- Handful of granola + berries
- *Total: ~32g protein, ~450 kcal*

**Option C — Shake (1 min):**
- 1 scoop whey + banana + water (30g protein)
- 2 hard-boiled eggs (12g protein)
- *Total: ~42g protein, ~400 kcal*

---

### Mid-Morning Snack (10 AM) — 20-27g protein

- 1 scoop whey protein with water (25g)
- 1 medium apple
- 10 almonds (pre-portioned)
- *Total: ~27g protein, ~280 kcal*

---

### Lunch (12-2 PM) — 35-52g protein

**LivUp Turbinada 370g** (microwave 5-6 min)

| Meal | Protein | Calories |
|------|:-------:|:--------:|
| Frango grelhado, arroz com brócolis e creme de milho | 52g | 477 |
| Frango assado, purê de batata doce e brócolis | 52g | 485 |
| Coxa de frango, arroz, feijão carioca e farofa | 37g | 440 |
| Carne moída, arroz integral e feijão carioca | 30g | 450 |

---

### Pre-Workout Snack (Training Days Only) — 17-27g protein

**Option A:** Greek yogurt + banana (~17g protein, 250 kcal)
**Option B:** Whey shake + banana (~27g protein, 280 kcal)

---

### Dinner (6-8 PM) — 40-52g protein

**Regular Days:** LivUp Turbinada (same options as lunch)

**Cheat Meal Days (2-3x/week on active days):**
- **Thursday:** Pizza (3 slices Frango Catupiry) ~45g protein
- **Friday:** Gourmet burger (no fries) ~45g protein
- **Saturday:** Churrascaria (lean cuts: picanha sem gordura, maminha, fraldinha) ~80g protein

---

### Evening Snack (Optional, 9-10 PM) — 20-25g protein

*Only if you haven't hit 154g yet*

- Cottage cheese 150g (~18g protein)
- Greek yogurt (~17g protein)
- Whey shake (~25g protein)

---

## Weekly Schedule

| Day | Activity | Lunch | Dinner | Protein |
|:---:|----------|-------|--------|:-------:|
| Mon | Lower A (Hinge + Glutes) | LivUp Turbinada | LivUp Turbinada | ~155g |
| Tue | Pilates + Daily Hip Routine | LivUp Turbinada | LivUp Turbinada | ~155g |
| Wed | Push (Upper Conditioning) | LivUp Turbinada | LivUp Turbinada | ~155g |
| Thu | Golf Lesson | LivUp Turbinada | Pizza | ~150g |
| Fri | Lower B (Squat + Stability) | LivUp Turbinada | Burger | ~155g |
| Sat | Pull OR Zone 2 + Optional Golf | Light lunch | Churrasco | ~150g |
| Sun | Zone 2 OR Golf OR Rest | Light lunch | Light | ~140g |

**Weekend Rule:**
- Pull on Saturday if fresh; otherwise Zone 2 + golf
- Skip Zone 2 on days you walk a full round
- Sunday is flexible recovery

---

## Training Program

### Conditioning Block (4-6 Weeks) — Back-Friendly, High-Variability Prep Phase

**Purpose:** Build tissue tolerance, movement quality, and work capacity before higher-intensity strength blocks.

### Block Principles
- Rep ranges mostly 10-12; finishers 15-25
- 2-4 reps in reserve on all sets
- No grinding or maxing
- Movement quality > load
- Intentional variability via A/B rotations (Weeks 1-2 = A / Weeks 3-4 = B)

---

### Daily Hip Routine (5 min — Do Every Day)

| Exercise | Reps/Duration |
|----------|:-------------:|
| Cat-Cow | 6-8 |
| Glute Bridges | 15 |
| 90/90 Hip Stretch | 30 sec/side |
| Bodyweight Good Mornings | 10 |

---

### Monday — Lower A (Hinge + Glutes)

| Exercise (A) | Exercise (B) | Sets | Reps |
|--------------|--------------|:----:|:----:|
| Barbell Hip Thrust | Banded or DB Hip Thrust | 3-4 | 10-12 |
| DB Romanian Deadlift | Kickstand RDL | 3 | 10-12 |
| Step-Ups | Reverse Lunges | 3 | 10/leg |
| Glute Bridges or Frog Pumps | — | 2 | 20-25 |
| Bird Dogs | — | 2 | 8/side |

---

### Tuesday — Pilates + Daily Hip Routine

- Full Pilates session
- Focus: Core control, hip stability, spinal mobility
- Do Daily Hip Routine

---

### Wednesday — Push (Upper Conditioning)

| Exercise (A) | Exercise (B) | Sets | Reps |
|--------------|--------------|:----:|:----:|
| Barbell Bench Press | DB Bench Press | 3-4 | 10-12 |
| DB Overhead Press | Arnold Press | 3 | 10 |
| Incline DB Bench Press | — | 3 | 12 |
| Lateral Raises | — | 2-3 | 15-20 |
| Triceps (rope or overhead DB) | — | 2 | 15-20 |

---

### Thursday — Golf Lesson

- Technique-focused session
- No heavy lifting
- Optional: Light walk, gentle stretching, Daily Hip Routine

---

### Friday — Lower B (Squat + Stability)

| Exercise (A) | Exercise (B) | Sets | Reps |
|--------------|--------------|:----:|:----:|
| Goblet Squat | Heel-Elevated Goblet Squat | 4 | 10 |
| Bulgarian Split Squat | Front-Foot-Elevated Split Squat | 3 | 8-10/leg |
| Single-Leg DB RDL | Cable Pull-Through | 3 | 10-12 |
| Side Plank | — | 2 | 30-45 sec/side |

---

### Saturday — Pull (Upper Back Conditioning)

| Exercise (A) | Exercise (B) | Sets | Reps |
|--------------|--------------|:----:|:----:|
| Pull-Ups | Neutral-Grip Lat Pulldown | 3-4 | 8-12 |
| Chest-Supported DB Row | Single-Arm Cable Row | 3 | 10-12 |
| Seated Cable Row (neutral) | — | 3 | 12-15 |
| Rear Delt Flyes | — | 2 | 15-20 |
| Hammer Curls | — | 2 | 15-20 |

---

### Zone 2 Cardio (1× / Week, 20 min)

**Intensity:** Conversational pace (Zone 2)

**Options:**
- Incline treadmill walk (2.5-3.2 mph, 6-10% incline) — preferred
- Stairmaster (slow, light rail use)
- Bike / Spin

**Placement:** Saturday (if skipping Pull) or Sunday

---

### Golf

- Thursday: Golf lesson
- Weekend: Play 9 or 18 holes
- Skip Zone 2 on days you walk a full round

---

## Supplements

| Supplement | Dose | Timing | Priority |
|------------|------|--------|:--------:|
| **Creatine Monohydrate** | 5g/day | Any time | Essential |
| **Caffeine** | 150-200mg | 30-60 min pre-workout | Essential |
| **Magnesium Citrate** | 400-500mg | Morning | Essential |
| **Magnesium Oxide** | 400-500mg | Evening | Essential |
| **Vitamin D3** | 2,000-4,000 IU | If deficient (<30 ng/mL) | Conditional |

> **Magnesium Note (Attia Protocol):** Total ~800-1000mg/day split between citrate (better absorbed) and oxide (gut health). Supports sleep, muscle recovery, and insulin sensitivity.

**Skip:** Extra protein powder (you hit 154g from food), pre-workout blends, HMB

---

## Shopping & Ordering

### LivUp Orders (Every 10 Days)

**Kit 20 Marmitas Turbinadas (370g)** — R$ 399,80
- 2 meals/day × 10 days = 20 meals
- Order link: https://www.livup.com.br

**Kit Proteínas Variadas (10 portions)** — for breakfast protein boost

**Proteins:**
- [ ] Eggs: 30/week (3 dozen)
- [ ] Greek Yogurt: 7-10 pots (170g each)
- [ ] Cottage Cheese: 2 pots (400g)
- [ ] Whey Protein: 1kg bag (lasts 1 month)

**Produce:**
- [ ] Bananas: 7-10
- [ ] Mixed berries (frozen OK)
- [ ] Avocados: 3-4
- [ ] Salad greens: 3 packs

**Carbs & Fats:**
- [ ] Oats: 500g bag
- [ ] Mixed nuts: 200g
- [ ] Peanut butter: 500g

**Supplements:**
- [ ] Magnesium Citrate (Now brand): 400mg capsules
- [ ] Magnesium Oxide (Carlson brand): 400mg capsules

---

## Tracking Protocol

### Daily (1 min)
- Morning weight (fasted, after bathroom)
- Log in Happy Scale (iOS) or Libra (Android)

### Weekly (Sunday)
- Calculate 7-day weight average
- Target: +0.25-0.5kg/week

### Bi-Weekly (Every 2 Sundays)
**Progress Photos (4 angles):**
1. Front relaxed
2. Side relaxed
3. Back relaxed
4. Front flexed

**Body Measurements:**
| Location | How to Measure | Target 4-Month Change |
|----------|----------------|:---------------------:|
| Chest | Widest part, across nipples | +3-6cm |
| Waist | At belly button, relaxed | +0-2cm |
| Right Arm | Mid-bicep, flexed | +2-3cm |
| Right Thigh | Mid-thigh, standing | +3-5cm |

### Quarterly — Blood Work (Critical for Diabetes Prevention)

| Test | Goal | Why |
|------|------|-----|
| Fasting glucose | <100 mg/dL | Diabetes marker |
| HbA1c | <5.7% | 3-month glucose average |
| Fasting insulin | <25 μIU/mL | Insulin resistance |
| HOMA-IR | <2.0 | Insulin sensitivity index |
| 25-hydroxyvitamin D | >30 ng/mL | Supplement if low |

**Expected improvements after 3 months:**
- Fasting glucose: ↓ 5-10 mg/dL
- HbA1c: ↓ 0.2-0.4%
- HOMA-IR: ↓ 20-30%

---

## Adjustment Guidelines

- 7-day weight average up 0.25-0.5kg/week
- Strength increasing 5-10%/month
- Waist stable or <0.5cm increase/month

- Reduce calories by 150-200
- Skip 1 afternoon snack OR add 20 min cardio

- Add 200-300 calories
- Extra protein portion at snack OR cup of rice at dinner

- Huberman Lab: Dr. Layne Norton, Dr. Gabrielle Lyon, Dr. Andy Galpin
- Low-GI emphasis for diabetes prevention

# Claro Daily Check-in Workflow

> Reference doc for how the daily check-in should work, based on actual Claude Code sessions.

---

## Session Startup

**Trigger:** "Fire up the pod" / "Daily check-in" / "Load up Obsidian vault"

**What happens:**
1. Load today's daily note (create from template if doesn't exist)
2. Show quick status:
   - Git status (if relevant)
   - Task Dashboard highlights (Top 3 projects, overdue items)
   - Today's note status (empty vs partially filled)
3. Prompt: "Ready for the brain dump" or "What's on your mind?"

---

## Brain Dump Phase

**User input style:** Stream of consciousness, voice transcription, messy thoughts

**What Claro does:**
1. Listen and capture everything
2. Parse into structured categories:
   - **Work tasks/projects** (with project tags)
   - **Personal items**
   - **Admin/errands**
   - **Waiting on / blocked items**
   - **Ideas for later**
3. Write to Raw Dump section of daily note
4. Extract actionable items into Organized Tasks section
5. Suggest Top 3 priorities based on what was dumped

**Example exchange:**
```
User: "Yeah so I'm gonna redo this project, want to ship it but need to use it
for a week first. Also the restaurant mapping thing morphed too much, going
back to v1. Working on that until 1pm. Oh and later I want to work on Clay."

Claro captures:
- Clay project: iterate before shipping, use for 1 week, match Obsidian workflow
- Restaurant mapping: back to v1, rebuild from there (NOW - until 1pm)
- Writes to daily note, sets Top 3
```

---

## Meal/Health Tracking

**Trigger:** User mentions food, meals, what they ate

**What Claro does:**
1. Accept input in any format:
   - Text description ("2 eggs, bread, bacon, some cake")
   - Image upload (parse nutrition labels, estimate portions)
   - Links to products
2. Estimate macros (calories, protein, carbs, fat)
3. Reference user's targets from their Muscle Building Program or diet plan
4. Calculate running totals vs daily targets
5. Provide rest-of-day guidance:
   - What's remaining in each macro
   - Specific meal suggestions that fit the gap
   - Flag constraints (e.g., "you're near your fat limit")

**Example exchange:**
```
User: [uploads image of Liv Up meal box]
"Had this for lunch, also had eggs and cake at breakfast"

Claro:
- Parses nutrition label from image (430g, 542 kcal, 35g protein)
- Estimates breakfast (~845 kcal, 30g protein)
- Shows running total vs 2,850 kcal / 154g protein targets
- Suggests: "You need 89g more protein. Options: Shake at 4pm + lean dinner..."
```

---

## Nutrition Science Integration

**When user asks "should I..." questions:**
- Reference stored knowledge (Attia protocols, Huberman, etc.)
- Apply to their specific situation
- Give actionable answer, not just theory

**Example:**
```
User: "Should I stack protein shake now since I only got 35g at lunch?"

Claro: "No - Attia says hit leucine threshold (~40g) then wait 4-5h for mTOR
reset. 35g is close enough. Take shake at 4pm for second MPS spike, dinner
for third. 3 spikes > 2 bigger ones."
```

---

## Project Management

**Stored project context:**
- Each project has its own file with goals, status, blockers
- Projects can be "recurring" (workout, diet) or "active" (shipping Claro)
- Projects integrate into daily check-in prompts

**What Claro tracks per project:**
- Current status / phase
- Blockers
- Next actions
- Recent progress
- How it connects to daily priorities

**Example recurring project integration:**
```
Morning check-in automatically includes:
- "Workout: What's today's session?" (pulls from program)
- "Diet: Log breakfast to start tracking"
- "Claro: Any progress on shipping?"
```

---

## Key Behaviors

### Be Conversational
- Accept messy voice input
- Don't require structured formats
- Parse intent from natural language

### Be Proactive
- Calculate totals automatically
- Flag issues ("you're over on fat")
- Suggest next actions

### Reference Context
- Know the user's programs, targets, projects
- Apply stored frameworks (Attia, etc.) to live questions
- Connect today's tasks to bigger goals

### Update in Real-Time
- Write to daily note as conversation progresses
- Don't wait until end of session
- Keep running totals current

### Stay Practical
- Give specific recommendations, not just information
- "Eat X" not "you need more protein"
- Time-bound suggestions ("shake at 4pm")

---

## Data Structure

### Daily Note
- Brain dump (raw + prompts)
- Top 3 priorities
- Health tracking (weight, meals, workout)
- Organized tasks (actions, waiting, delegate, quick wins)
- Captured for later (projects, someday, notes)
- End of day reflection

### Project Files
- One file per active project
- Contains: goals, current status, blockers, next actions, history

### Reference Files
- Muscle Building Program (targets, meal structure, training)
- Diet protocols
- Weekly review template
- Hotspots (areas of focus)
